# For Osiris-enabled deployments, Osiris automatically instruments application pods. When Osiris determines that a deploymentâ€™s
# pods are idle, Osiris scales the deployment to zero replicas.

# He mentions that one use-case for project Osiris is with virtualnodes which uses ACI (billed per second)
# e.g. multiple replicas not being used when configured through virtualnodes, which decreases the replica count to 0,
# thus reducing cost even further.

# May be a fit for certain serverless workloads which run on top of k8s - knative, kubeless, OpenFaas...

